

 Q1. Explain about the life-cycle of a Spring Bean.
 
 Answer)  For simple java classes constructor and finalize() methods is the  life cycle methods that is called by JVM automatically. In spring spring
          container controls the spring bean life-cycle. There is initalization and destroy methods.
          
          
			There are 5 stages of spring bean class in life cycle :- 
			
			1. Not exist :- At first there s no spring bean object exist.if bean object is singleton scope bean will load by container at a time of 
			                loading xml file else if it is prototype then load by conataiiner at a time of pulling object.
			                
			2)Instansiate :- 
			3)intialized
			4)service
			5)Destroy
			 
 